label.value: circuit part of central nervous system

value.value: A collection of neuronal components interacting in a functional circuit. A neural circuit is bounded by the nervous sytem regions in which its participating neuronal components are contained (BB).

label.value: ganglion part of peripheral nervous system

value.value: A spatially aggregated collection of nerve cell body parts in the PNS, consisting of one or more subpopulations that share cell type, chemical phenotype, and connections. (CUMBO).
The part of the central nervous system that is involved with movement.

definition.value: It consists of the pyramidal and extrapyramidal system

value.value: The sensory system for the sense of proprioception.

label.value: perirhinal cortex of primate of Burwell et al 1995

value.value: Cortical region near the rhinal sulcus in primate encompassing Brodmann's areas 35 and 36.

label.value: perirhinal cortex of rodent of Burwell et al 1995

value.value: Cortical region surrounding the posterior rhinal sulcus in the rat, encompassing areas 35 and 36 in the rat. Rostraly, it abuts the posterior insular cortex.
Any molecule, protein, cell, tissue or organ that is related to histamine.
Any molecule, protein, cell, tissue or organ that is related to the catecholamines.
Any molecule, protein, cell, tissue or organ that is related to GABA.
Any molecule, protein, cell, tissue or organ that is related to glutamate (when in the role of a neurotransmitter).
Any molecule, protein, cell, tissue or organ that is related to serotonin.
Any molecule, protein, cell, tissue or organ that is related to acetylcholine.

label.value: paravermis parts of the cerebellar cortex

value.value: Sulcus in the frontal lobe of the macaque. (Brain Info).

label.value: dorsal nerve root of lumbar spinal cord

value.value: A neuronal circuit bearing a principal projection neuron whose axon extends beyond the region where its soma is located to synapse on the dendrites of cells in other regions of the nervous system (BB).
A neuronal circuit where all the participating neurons are bounded within a defined and limited region of the nervous system.(BB).

A minute canal that passes from the petrous portion of the temporal bone between the jugular fossa and carotid canal to the floor of the tympanic cavity and transmits the tympanic branch of the glossopharyngeal nerve.
The division of the spiral canal of the cochlea lying above the spiral lamina and the vestibular membrane.
A superficial feature of the frontal lobe that extends from the dorsal surface onto the medial surface of the superior frontal gyrus (Ono-90). (NN).
A sulcus in the human parietal lobe that branches dorsally from the intraparietal sulcus (Savel'ev-96). (NN).
A superficial feature of the parietal lobe that extends from the dorsal surface of the superior parietal lobule across the margin of the parietal lobe into the precuneus (Ono-90). (NN).
A superficial feature of the parietal lobe. It is the portion of the superior temporal sulcus that extends into the angular gyrus (Ono-90). (NN).
